<paragraph blockId="224.[151,1437,402,2014]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[624,846,618,644]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Guineafowl Puffer</emphasis>
or Guineafowl Pufferfish. To 
<quantity box="[1184,1253,618,645]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" unit="cm" value="45.0">45 cm</quantity>
TL (
<quantity box="[1308,1388,619,646]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4958" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" unit="in" value="17.7">17.7 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Kuiter and Tonozuka" box="[205,511,655,681]" firstAuthor="Kuiter" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" refId="ref292824" refString="Kuiter, R. H. &amp; Tonozuka, T. (2001) Pictorial Guide to Indonesian Reef Fishes. Zoonetic, Seaford, Victoria." type="book" year="2001">Kuiter and Tonozuka 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Indo-Pacific; western Pacific Ocean north to Ogasawara Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1329,655,681]" name="Japan" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Yamada in 
<bibRefCitation author="Nakabo" box="[229,386,691,717]" firstAuthor="Nakabo" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" refId="ref304533" refString="Nakabo, T. (Ed.). (2002) Fishes of Japan with Pictorial Keys to the Species. Tokai University Press, Tokyo." type="book" year="2002">Nakabo 2002</bibRefCitation>
); Todos Santos area (
<geoCoordinate box="[632,753,691,717]" degrees="23" direction="north" minutes="24.6" orientation="latitude" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" precision="92" value="23.41">23°24.6’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[767,905,691,717]" degrees="110" direction="west" minutes="13.8" orientation="longitude" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" precision="92" value="-110.23">110°13.8’W</geoCoordinate>
) (Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California); tip of Baja California into central and southern Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson and Allen" box="[327,626,763,789]" firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" refId="ref316713" refString="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Allen, G. R. (2002) Shorefishes of the tropical eastern Pacific: an information system. CD-ROM. Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa, Panama." type="book" year="2002">Robertson and Allen 2002</bibRefCitation>
) to Peru (
<bibRefCitation author="Pequeno" box="[738,904,763,789]" firstAuthor="Pequeno" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref311468" refString="Pequeno R., G. (1989) Peces de Chile lista sistematica revisada y comentada. Revista de Biologia Marina y Oceanografia, 24, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1989">Pequeño 1989</bibRefCitation>
), including Islas Galápagos, and other offshore islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson and Allen" box="[290,592,799,825]" firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" refId="ref316713" refString="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Allen, G. R. (2002) Shorefishes of the tropical eastern Pacific: an information system. CD-ROM. Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa, Panama." type="book" year="2002">Robertson and Allen 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Benthic; depth: 1–144 (
<quantity box="[876,974,799,826]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.239" metricValueMax="14.38656" metricValueMin="0.09144" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" unit="ft" value="237.5" valueMax="472.0" valueMin="3.0">3–472 ft</quantity>
) (min.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson and Allen" box="[1063,1362,799,825]" firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" refId="ref316713" refString="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Allen, G. R. (2002) Shorefishes of the tropical eastern Pacific: an information system. CD-ROM. Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa, Panama." type="book" year="2002">Robertson and Allen 2002</bibRefCitation>
; max.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Weijerman" box="[198,455,835,861]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Weijerman" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" pagination="161 - 182" refId="ref332632" refString="Weijerman, M., Gruss, A., Dove, D., Asher, J., Williams, I. D., Kelley, C. &amp; Drazen, J. (2019) Shining a light on the composition and distribution patterns of mesophotic and subphotic fish communities in Hawai'i. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 630, 161 - 182. https: // doi. org / 10.3354 / meps 13135" type="journal article" year="2019">
Weijerman 
<emphasis box="[328,386,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). The original description is usually ascribed to Lacepède; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke" box="[1125,1346,835,861]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Fricke" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" refId="ref280407" refString="Fricke, R., Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; van der Laan, R. (Eds). 2020. Eschmeyer's Catalog of Fishes: Genera, Species, Reference. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp (accessed 17 April 2021)." type="url" year="2020">
Fricke 
<emphasis box="[1205,1263,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
explain why Anonymous is correct.
</paragraph>
